@startuml fig-A08-message-flow
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title VXLAN Tunnel — E2 PCAP Flow (Encapsulation and Connectivity)

participant "h1\nSite A\n10.100.0.1" as H1 #FFE0B2
participant "r1\nVTEP A\n172.16.0.1" as R1 #E1BEE7
participant "Underlay\n(capture point)" as UL #ECEFF1
participant "r2\nVTEP B\n172.16.0.2" as R2 #E1BEE7
participant "h2\nSite B\n10.100.0.2" as H2 #FFE0B2

== ARP RESOLUTION (overlay) ==

H1 -> R1 : ARP: who has 10.100.0.2?
R1 -> UL : outer: 172.16.0.1 → 172.16.0.2\nUDP/4789 | VXLAN VNI=1010\ninner: ARP Request
UL -> R2 : forwarded on underlay
R2 -> H2 : ARP Request (decapsulated)
H2 --> R2 : ARP Reply
R2 -> UL : outer: 172.16.0.2 → 172.16.0.1\nUDP/4789 | VXLAN VNI=1010\ninner: ARP Reply
UL -> R1 : forwarded
R1 --> H1 : ARP Reply (decapsulated)
note right of UL : R2: arp || icmp >= 1

== ICMP PING (overlay through tunnel) ==

H1 -[#43A047]> R1 : ICMP Echo 10.100.0.1 → 10.100.0.2
R1 -[#43A047]> UL : outer: 172.16.0.1 → 172.16.0.2\nUDP/4789 | VNI=1010\ninner: ICMP Echo
note right of UL #E8F5E9 : R1: udp.port==4789 >= 5
UL -> R2 : underlay delivery
R2 -[#43A047]> H2 : ICMP Echo (decapsulated)
H2 -[#43A047]-> R2 : ICMP Reply
R2 -> UL : VXLAN encapsulated reply
UL -> R1 : forwarded
R1 -[#43A047]-> H1 : ICMP Reply

== PACKET STRUCTURE (observed at capture point) ==

note over UL #FFF9C4
  Outer: Ethernet | IP (172.16.x) | UDP/4789
  VXLAN: VNI=1010 | Flags
  Inner: Ethernet | IP (10.100.x) | ICMP
end note

legend right
  PCAP on underlay interface shows
  outer UDP/4789 with VXLAN header (VNI)
  wrapping the original Ethernet frame.
  Both ARP and ICMP traverse the tunnel.
endlegend
@enduml
